{
  "texts": [
    "However, recent studies indicated that drugs typically influenced related pathways rather than single targets, prompting the introduction of a new strategy called pathway-based",
    "Naïve Bayes (NB) model.",
    "NB 49, 50 is a widely used method for classification and is particularly suitable when the input dimensionality is high.",
    "Despite its simplicity, NB can often outperform more complex classification techniques.",
    "It measures the probability of each input feature (attribute) for a predictable state."
  ]
}